.TH GH-MAKERELEASE 1 "2026-03-01" "gh-makerelease 1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gh-makerelease \- create a GitHub release with auto-detected project type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gh-makerelease
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gh-makerelease
detects the project type at the repository root (\fIdebian\fR, \fIvsix\fR, or
\fInodejs\fR), builds artifacts, tags \fIvVERSION\fR, and creates a GitHub
release with a source tarball and build outputs. Requires \fBgh\fR(1)
authenticated for GitHub.
.PP
For \fIdebian\fR projects it runs \fBdebuild\fR(1) or
\fBdpkg-buildpackage\fR(1); for \fIvsix\fR and \fInodejs\fR it runs
\fBpnpm package\fR. Release notes come from \fIdebian/changelog\fR (debian)
or the latest commit message (vsix/nodejs).
.SS VSIX extensions
After a successful \fBpnpm package\fR, when not using \fB\-l\fR
(\fB\-\-local\fR), the extension is published to the Visual Studio Marketplace
(\fBvsce publish\fR) and to Open VSX (\fBovsx publish\fR) when credentials are
available.
.PP
Personal access tokens are read from the first non-empty line of each file:
.IP \[bu] 2
\fI~/.identity/azure-devops.id\fR \- Azure DevOps PAT with Marketplace
(Manage) scope for \fBvsce\fR(1) (\fBVSCE_PAT\fR).
.IP \[bu]
\fI~/.identity/open-vsx.id\fR \- Open VSX token for \fBovsx\fR(1)
(\fBOVSX_PAT\fR).
.PP
If a file is missing or empty, that registry is skipped with a log message.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-no-pre-clean\fR
Reuse build cache (passed through to Debian builds).
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-unsigned\fR
Build unsigned Debian packages (\fB\-us \-uc\fR).
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-local\fR
Build only; do not tag, push, publish to marketplaces, or create a GitHub release.
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-force\fR
If the release or tag already exists, delete it and recreate. Use with care.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose logging to stderr.
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Reduce verbosity.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print usage and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success; non-zero on error (invalid options, not a git repo, build
failure, marketplace publish failure, \fBgh\fR not authenticated, or release
creation failure).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR debuild (1),
.BR gh (1),
.BR git (1),
.BR ovsx (1),
.BR vsce (1),
